    <string name="card_include_label">Send card</string>
    <string name="card_include_off_hint">Without the card, the link moves into the post text.</string>
    <string name="card_include_help">What does “Send card” do?</string>
    <string name="card_include_help_text">Bluesky does not build the link preview itself, Scatter sends it along. With the switch on, a card with image, title and description appears below the post, and the link is NOT in the text. That saves about 50 characters.\n\nWith the switch off, the post goes out without a card and the URL moves back into the text. Useful when the card does not fit or the page has no usable image.\n\nMastodon has no such switch: there the server builds the preview itself from the linked page.</string>

    <string name="regen_confirm_title">Discard edited texts?</string>
